1
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,719
Why is Commander Chen turning off?

2
00:00:50,039 --> 00:00:51,560
What's he up to?

3
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,000
No idea.

4
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,280
Where's he driving off to?

5
00:01:01,159 --> 00:01:02,520
Fatty, Shu Tong.

6
00:01:03,359 --> 00:01:04,280
Don't worry.

7
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:06,000
I'm meeting a friend.

8
00:01:06,599 --> 00:01:08,480
Tell Uncle Min the plan stays the same.

9
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:11,200
We meet at Tiger's Mouth River in two days.

10
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:12,200
Fatty.

11
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:14,319
Drive carefully.

12
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:15,640
See you in two days.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:18,480
Hey, Chen Youxi, hey!

14
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:22,239
Boss, we lost the rear car.

15
00:01:36,719 --> 00:01:37,519
Fatty.

16
00:01:38,079 --> 00:01:40,439
Why can't I see Brother Chen's car?

17
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:42,200
Well, well...

18
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:46,280
Uncle Min, it's nothing.

19
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:47,879
Just relax.

20
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,680
That Brother Chen is a real ladies' man.

21
00:01:50,959 --> 00:01:52,959
He's got a sweetheart around here.

22
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:57,159
He took a detour to see her.

23
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:58,840
But the plan stays the same.

24
00:01:58,840 --> 00:02:01,079
We meet at Tiger's Mouth River in two days.

25
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,480
Don't worry, sir.

26
00:02:46,439 --> 00:02:47,080
Dawang!

27
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:50,840
Don't run! Stop!

28
00:02:53,319 --> 00:02:55,240
Dawang, if you dare, don't run!

29
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,479
You hurt two of my brothers.

30
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:03,599
I'm not done with you today.

31
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:16,680
Go!

32
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,680
Don't run! Stop!

33
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:52,919
Brother.

34
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:55,360
You really think highly of me.

35
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,280
Bringing so many men after me.

36
00:03:57,719 --> 00:03:58,800
Cut the crap.

37
00:03:59,159 --> 00:04:00,879
Dawang, you can't escape.

38
00:04:01,039 --> 00:04:02,400
You hurt two of my brothers.

39
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,319
I'm gonna kill you today.

40
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,080
Fine.

41
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:09,080
You can kill me.

42
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,520
But tell your brothers to fall back.

43
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,599
Don't let them die for nothing.

44
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:14,599
Brother.

45
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,240
If you're a real man,

46
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,839
let's settle this one-on-one.

47
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:18,519
What do you say?

48
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,279
Go, quick!

49
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,680
Calling for reinforcements?

50
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,639
Look out!

51
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:57,920
Come here.

52
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,519
Who are they?

53
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:10,639
Poachers.

54
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:12,680
I caught their boss a few days ago.

55
00:05:12,759 --> 00:05:13,720
They're here for revenge.

56
00:05:16,079 --> 00:05:17,160
Isn't that mine?

57
00:05:17,199 --> 00:05:18,560
It's our love token.

58
00:05:19,399 --> 00:05:20,120
Dawang!

59
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:22,600
You gonna hide in there like a coward?

60
00:05:22,879 --> 00:05:23,920
If you don't come out,

61
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,279
I'll burn you alive!

62
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,519
We can't hold out.

63
00:05:26,519 --> 00:05:28,120
Same as always: one, two, three.

64
00:05:28,439 --> 00:05:30,079
One, two, three!

65
00:05:31,279 --> 00:05:32,079
What the hell?

66
00:05:32,120 --> 00:05:33,319
What "same as always"?

67
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,680
Cover me, cover me!

68
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:35,879
Why didn't you just say so?

69
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:40,680
Look out!

70
00:05:50,879 --> 00:05:51,560
Again!

71
00:05:59,480 --> 00:05:59,920
Fall back!

72
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:00,839
This one's tough.

73
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,160
You just wait.

74
00:06:02,439 --> 00:06:03,800
I'll be back.

75
00:06:03,879 --> 00:06:04,519
Fall back!

76
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:17,800
Old Chen.

77
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,319
Since we took that photo together,

78
00:06:20,519 --> 00:06:21,759
we haven't had a drink, have we?

79
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,800
A man in uniform really does look sharp.

80
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,480
Out with it.

81
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:34,639
You came all this way to find me.

82
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:36,000
There must be something else.

83
00:06:36,199 --> 00:06:36,879
Speak.

84
00:06:38,839 --> 00:06:40,120
I need to go to Mengna Valley.

85
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:44,319
I've looked through a lot of records.

86
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:46,600
Mengna Valley has no historical records.

87
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,519
Only your local elders would know about it,

88
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:51,839
in the Epic of the Enemy-Subduing Lord,

89
00:06:51,839 --> 00:06:52,759
that's where it's recorded.

90
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,279
I figured since you've been here for years,

91
00:06:55,439 --> 00:06:56,480
you might know something

92
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,879
about Mengna Valley.

93
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,519
Legend says

94
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:05,040
demons are sealed inside Mengna Valley.

95
00:07:05,639 --> 00:07:07,199
Throughout history, many high monks

96
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:08,439
sought to protect the dharma and slay demons,

97
00:07:08,439 --> 00:07:10,000
to wipe out Mengna Valley,

98
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,839
to stop the evil god from returning.

99
00:07:11,839 --> 00:07:12,639
But

100
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,600
not one of them succeeded.

101
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,839
You're not even afraid of poachers,

102
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,920
yet this nonsense has got you so spooked?

103
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,360
Old Chen,

104
00:07:24,199 --> 00:07:25,439
that's a different matter entirely.

105
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,879
I can't say what might happen

106
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:29,120
on the way to Mengna Valley.

107
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:30,560
And I really can't say

108
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,560
if disturbing the ruins of Mengna Valley

109
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,399
might trigger a chain of disasters.

110
00:07:34,920 --> 00:07:35,959
Besides,

111
00:07:36,079 --> 00:07:38,560
Mengna Valley is taboo around here.

112
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,079
My advice is,

113
00:07:40,639 --> 00:07:41,759
you really shouldn't go.

114
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,279
Don't try to talk me out of it.

115
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,720
This is my last archaeological survey.

116
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,759
I've made up my mind. I have to go.

117
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,279
Alright.

118
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,279
When I get back from Mengna Valley,

119
00:07:54,279 --> 00:07:55,240
I'll have a proper drink with you.

120
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,199
Take care of yourself.

121
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,360
What took you so long?

122
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:15,680
Why haven't you left yet?

123
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,040
Going through hell for a brother,

124
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,120
that's the you I know.

125
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:26,720
What's in this big bag?

126
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:28,519
Booze.

127
00:08:52,639 --> 00:08:54,519
Hey, Old Chen's back!

128
00:08:54,639 --> 00:08:55,840
Old Chen's back!

129
00:08:58,879 --> 00:09:00,639
Old Chen, over here, over here!

130
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,039
This way, this way!

131
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,360
Here, here, stop here!

132
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,320
Hey, Commander Chen,

133
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,840
why'd you leave without a word?

134
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:22,759
Wait...

135
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,039
Dawang?

136
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,720
Old Chen, this is...

137
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,600
Dawang.

138
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:28,639
An old army brother of mine and Fatty's.

139
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,240
Mr. Da,

140
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,879
it's an honor.

141
00:09:32,159 --> 00:09:33,039
His surname isn't Da.

142
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,720
Look at his physique,

143
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,039
he's tough and straight-up. Over time,

144
00:09:36,039 --> 00:09:37,360
all us brothers just started calling him that.

145
00:09:37,559 --> 00:09:39,279
Get out of here. What brothers?

146
00:09:39,519 --> 00:09:40,639
He's no brother of mine.

147
00:09:43,879 --> 00:09:45,960
I knew Brother Chen would come back.

148
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,399
He went to get us some outside help.

149
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,600
You two have bad blood?

150
00:09:54,919 --> 00:09:55,919
Of course.

151
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,679
Otherwise, would I act like that?

152
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:58,600
What do you mean?

153
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,000
Back in our army days,

154
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:03,679
this bastard stole my girl.

155
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,399
You think I could just be all chummy with him?

156
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:08,919
No way, no way.

157
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,799
Exactly.

158
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:20,159
The new guy's carrying a weapon.

159
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:21,759
We need to keep a close eye on him.

160
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:22,919
Got it.

161
00:10:23,399 --> 00:10:24,600
Once we find the Silver Eye,

162
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:26,360
if anyone steps out of line,

163
00:10:26,799 --> 00:10:27,799
take them out immediately.

164
00:10:37,519 --> 00:10:39,120
We're almost at Juedabu Cheng.

165
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,159
This is the only way through.

166
00:10:41,759 --> 00:10:42,840
We can't drive any further.

167
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:44,000
We'll have to continue on foot.

168
00:10:45,159 --> 00:10:46,480
Everyone, watch your step.

169
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:48,159
The slope is pretty slippery.

170
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,440
One wrong move

171
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:51,960
and it could trigger a landslide.

172
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:56,480
Brother Lu, slow down!

173
00:10:57,039 --> 00:10:57,840
Watch your step!

174
00:11:17,279 --> 00:11:19,279
Everyone, be careful while climbing.

175
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,840
If the ground gives way under you

176
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,360
or you slip and fall,

177
00:11:22,799 --> 00:11:24,960
use your trekking pole to anchor yourself

178
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,759
and slow down your descent.

179
00:11:27,559 --> 00:11:28,480
Ms. He,

180
00:11:28,480 --> 00:11:29,720
that ice axe of yours

181
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:32,000
is meant for snowy mountain falls.

182
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:33,840
In a place like this,

183
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:36,879
I don't think it'll work as well.

184
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:44,679
Lao Lian, are you okay?

185
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:46,519
Godfather!

186
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:47,559
Impressive!

187
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,720
Brother Chen and Ms. He, a perfect match.

188
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,279
You two work so well together.

189
00:11:52,559 --> 00:11:54,039
That was eye-opening.

190
00:11:55,559 --> 00:11:56,879
Godfather, you alright? I'm fine, fine.

191
00:11:56,879 --> 00:11:57,360
Let's go.

192
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:58,279
Glad you're okay.

193
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,240
Made a fool of yourself, huh?

194
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:55,759
Here, take it.

195
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:57,720
Shu Tong.

196
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:01,879
Those two...

197
00:13:11,639 --> 00:13:12,440
Be careful.

198
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,120
This is the place.

199
00:13:18,519 --> 00:13:20,240
It's exactly like the photo

200
00:13:20,919 --> 00:13:22,279
Counselor He showed us.

